### merge() {#a771573ea5cd6f54eccf26c50dac5e049}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool llvm::DWARFAddressRange::merge (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/dwarfaddressrange">DWARFAddressRange</a> &amp; RHS)</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Union two address ranges if they intersect.

This function will union two address ranges if they intersect by modifying this range to be the union of both ranges. If the two ranges don&#39;t intersect this range will be left alone.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="RHS">Another address range to combine with.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
false if the ranges don&#39;t intersect, true if they do and the ranges were combined.
</SectionUser>
